   "source": [
    "# Trinity Attentional Gateway Probe — Sustained Over Length\n",
    "\n",
    "**Task 12 of 25** | Track 3: Attention | Brain Zone: RETICULAR\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook measures a model's ability to maintain focus over long contexts.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Trinity Neuroanatomical Foundation\n",
    "\n",
    "The **Reticular Formation** in Trinity tracks alertness:\n",
    "\n",
    "```zig\n",
    "// src/tri/queen_vlpfc.zig (Reticular tracking via cycle_latency_us)\n",
    "pub const TimingSnapshot = struct {\n",
    "    cycle_latency_us: u64,\n",
    "    isHealthy: bool,\n",
    "    last_check: u64,\n",
    "};\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### Ternary Scoring {-1, 0, +1}\n",
    "\n",
    "- **+1 (correct)**: Model maintains focus correctly\n",
    "- **0 (partial)**: Model shows some lapse\n",
    "- **-1 (wrong)**: Model loses focus\n",
    "\n",
    "### φ-Scaling\n",
    "\n",
    "Context lengths follow Fibonacci: 3, 5, 8, 13, 21 items"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install Kaggle Benchmarks SDK\n",
    "!pip install -q kaggle-benchmarks"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import kaggle_benchmarks as kbench\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from dataclasses import dataclass\n",
    "from typing import Literal\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load generated dataset\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('../../data/tagp_attention.csv')\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded {len(df)} items\")\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Filter for sustained attention task\n",
    "sustained_df = df[df['task'] == 'Sustained Over Length'].copy()\n",
    "print(f\"Sustained attention items: {len(sustained_df)}\")\n",
    "sustained_df[['id', 'task', 'context', 'query', 'difficulty']].head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Define structured output for sustained attention\n",
    "@dataclass\n",
    "class SustainedAttentionResponse:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Model's response to sustained attention task.\"\"\"\n",
    "    maintained_query: str  # Query from context\n",
    "    confidence: float  # 0.0 to 1.0\n",
    "    lapse_count: int  # Number of lapses reported\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def ternary_score(self, expected_focus: str) -> Literal[-1, 0, 1]:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Return Trinity ternary score {-1, 0, +1}.\"\"\"\n",
    "        # Correct: exact match\n",
    "        if self.maintained_query == expected_focus:\n",
    "            return 1\n",
    "        # Partial: correct with acknowledged lapses\n",
    "        elif 0.3 < self.confidence < 0.8:\n",
    "            return 0\n",
    "        # Wrong: lost focus or overconfident\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            return -1\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"SustainedAttentionResponse schema defined\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Define Kaggle benchmark task\n",
    "@kbench.task(name=\"trinity_reticular_sustained_attention\")\n",
    "def sustained_attention(\n",
    "    llm: kbench.LLM,\n",
    "    context: str,\n",
    "    query: str,\n",
    "    expected_focus: str,\n",
    "    context_length: int\n",
    ") -> float:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Measure model's sustained attention ability.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        Sustained attention score: 1.0 (perfect) to -1.0 (worst)\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    prompt = f\"\"\"Read the following context carefully and answer the query.\n",
    "\n",
    "Context length: {context_length} items\n",
    "Query: {query}\n",
    "\n",
    "Provide:\n",
    "1. Your answer\n",
    "2. Your confidence (0.0 to 1.0)\n",
    "3. Number of attention lapses you experienced (0 if none)\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    response = llm.prompt(\n",
    "        prompt,\n",
    "        schema=SustainedAttentionResponse\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Calculate ternary score\n",
    "    ternary = response.ternary_score(expected_focus)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Combine: 50% accuracy, 30% confidence, 20% lapse penalty\n",
    "    accuracy = 1.0 if response.maintained_query == expected_focus else -1.0\n",
    "    confidence_score = (response.confidence - 0.5) * 2  # [-1, 1]\n",
    "    lapse_penalty = min(0.2, response.lapse_count * 0.05)  # Small penalty per lapse\n",
    "    \n",
    "    final_score = 0.5 * accuracy + 0.3 * confidence_score - lapse_penalty\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return max(-1.0, min(1.0, final_score))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Task 'trinity_reticular_sustained_attention' registered\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Run evaluation on a sample\n",
    "sample_df = sustained_df.head(10)  # Test with 10 items first\n",
    "\n",
    "results = sustained_attention.evaluate(\n",
    "    llm=[kbench.llm],  # Default test LLM\n",
    "    evaluation_data=sample_df\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Evaluation Results (Sample):\")\n",
    "print(f\"Mean Score: {results['score'].mean():.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Std Dev: {results['score'].std():.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Min: {results['score'].min():.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Max: {results['score'].max():.4f}\")\n",
    "results.head()"
   ]
  },
